 "cells": [
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "# Clase 7: Matplotlib - Visualización de Datos\n",
    "\n",
    "## Objetivos\n",
    "- Crear gráficos básicos (líneas, dispersión, histogramas, cajas)\n",
    "- Visualizar distribuciones de datos\n",
    "- Explorar relaciones entre variables\n",
    "- Preparar visualizaciones para análisis de modelos de redes neuronales\n",
    "\n",
    "## ¿Por qué Matplotlib es importante?\n",
    "La visualización es crucial para:\n",
    "- **Entender los datos** antes de entrenar un modelo\n",
    "- **Detectar anomalías y patrones**\n",
    "- **Evaluar resultados** del entrenamiento de redes neuronales\n",
    "- **Comunicar hallazgos** de forma clara"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 1. Importar Matplotlib y Configurar\n",
    "\n",
    "Matplotlib es la librería estándar de visualización en Python."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "import matplotlib.pyplot as plt\n",
    "import numpy as np\n",
    "import pandas as pd\n",
    "\n",
    "# Configurar para que los gráficos se muestren en el notebook\n",
    "%matplotlib inline\n",
    "\n",
    "# Mejorar la apariencia de los gráficos\n",
    "plt.rcParams['figure.figsize'] = (10, 6)\n",
    "plt.rcParams['font.size'] = 11\n",
    "\n",
    "print(f\"Versión de Matplotlib: {plt.matplotlib.__version__}\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 2. Gráfico de Líneas (Line Plot)\n",
    "\n",
    "Ideal para mostrar tendencias en el tiempo o cambios de valores."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Datos: pérdida durante el entrenamiento de una red neuronal\n",
    "epocas = np.arange(1, 11)\n",
    "perdida_entrenamiento = [5.2, 4.8, 4.3, 3.9, 3.5, 3.2, 3.0, 2.9, 2.8, 2.8]\n",
    "perdida_validacion = [5.1, 4.9, 4.6, 4.2, 4.0, 3.9, 3.8, 3.8, 3.9, 4.0]\n",
    "\n",
    "# Crear figura\n",
    "plt.figure(figsize=(10, 6))\n",
    "\n",
    "# Graficar líneas\n",
    "plt.plot(epocas, perdida_entrenamiento, marker='o', label='Entrenamiento', linewidth=2)\n",
    "plt.plot(epocas, perdida_validacion, marker='s', label='Validación', linewidth=2)\n",
    "\n",
    "# Etiquetas y título\n",
    "plt.xlabel('Época')\n",
    "plt.ylabel('Pérdida')\n",
    "plt.title('Pérdida del Modelo Neural durante el Entrenamiento')\n",
    "plt.legend()\n",
    "plt.grid(True, alpha=0.3)\n",
    "plt.show()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 3. Gráfico de Dispersión (Scatter Plot)\n",
    "\n",
    "Muestra la relación entre dos variables."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Datos: relación entre horas de estudio y promedio\n",
    "np.random.seed(42)\n",
    "horas_estudio = np.random.uniform(1, 10, 50)\n",
    "promedio = 5 + 0.5 * horas_estudio + np.random.normal(0, 1, 50)\n",
    "\n",
    "plt.figure(figsize=(10, 6))\n",
    "\n",
    "# Scatter plot\n",
    "plt.scatter(horas_estudio, promedio, alpha=0.6, s=100, color='blue')\n",
    "\n",
    "# Añadir línea de tendencia\n",
    "z = np.polyfit(horas_estudio, promedio, 1)\n",
    "p = np.poly1d(z)\n",
    "plt.plot(horas_estudio, p(horas_estudio), \"r--\", linewidth=2, label='Línea de tendencia')\n",
    "\n",
    "plt.xlabel('Horas de Estudio')\n",
    "plt.ylabel('Promedio')\n",
    "plt.title('Relación entre Horas de Estudio y Promedio')\n",
    "plt.legend()\n",
    "plt.grid(True, alpha=0.3)\n",
    "plt.show()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 4. Histograma (Histogram)\n",
    "\n",
    "Muestra la distribución de una variable continua."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Datos: distribución de promedio de estudiantes\n",
    "np.random.seed(42)\n",
    "promedios = np.random.normal(7.5, 1.2, 200)\n",
    "promedios = np.clip(promedios, 0, 10)  # Limitar entre 0 y 10\n",
    "\n",
    "plt.figure(figsize=(10, 6))\n",
    "\n",
    "# Histograma\n",
    "plt.hist(promedios, bins=20, color='green', alpha=0.7, edgecolor='black')\n",
    "\n",
    "# Línea de media\n",
    "plt.axvline(promedios.mean(), color='red', linestyle='--', linewidth=2, label=f'Media: {promedios.mean():.2f}')\n",
    "plt.axvline(np.median(promedios), color='orange', linestyle='--', linewidth=2, label=f'Mediana: {np.median(promedios):.2f}')\n",
    "\n",
    "plt.xlabel('Promedio')\n",
    "plt.ylabel('Frecuencia')\n",
    "plt.title('Distribución de Promedios de Estudiantes')\n",
    "plt.legend()\n",
    "plt.grid(True, alpha=0.3, axis='y')\n",
    "plt.show()\n",
    "\n",
    "print(f\"Media: {promedios.mean():.2f}\")\n",
    "print(f\"Desv. Est.: {promedios.std():.2f}\")\n",
    "print(f\"Mín: {promedios.min():.2f}, Máx: {promedios.max():.2f}\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 5. Gráfico de Cajas (Box Plot)\n",
    "\n",
    "Muestra la distribución, mediana, cuartiles y outliers."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Datos: promedio por grupo\n",
    "np.random.seed(42)\n",
    "grupo_a = np.random.normal(7.5, 1.0, 100)\n",
    "grupo_b = np.random.normal(8.0, 1.2, 100)\n",
    "grupo_c = np.random.normal(6.8, 0.9, 100)\n",
    "\n",
    "plt.figure(figsize=(10, 6))\n",
    "\n",
    "# Box plot\n",
    "datos_box = [grupo_a, grupo_b, grupo_c]\n",
    "plt.boxplot(datos_box, labels=['Grupo A', 'Grupo B', 'Grupo C'], patch_artist=True)\n",
    "\n",
    "# Colorear las cajas\n",
    "for patch, color in zip(plt.gca().artists, ['lightblue', 'lightgreen', 'lightcoral']):\n",
    "    patch.set_facecolor(color)\n",
    "\n",
    "plt.ylabel('Promedio')\n",
    "plt.title('Distribución de Promedios por Grupo')\n",
    "plt.grid(True, alpha=0.3, axis='y')\n",
    "plt.show()\n",
    "\n",
    "# Estadísticas\n",
    "for i, (datos, nombre) in enumerate([(grupo_a, 'A'), (grupo_b, 'B'), (grupo_c, 'C')]):\n",
    "    print(f\"Grupo {nombre}: media={datos.mean():.2f}, std={datos.std():.2f}, min={datos.min():.2f}, max={datos.max():.2f}\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 6. Gráfico de Barras (Bar Chart)\n",
    "\n",
    "Compara valores categóricos."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Datos: promedio por región\n",
    "regiones = ['Norte', 'Sur', 'Este', 'Oeste']\n",
    "promedios_region = [7.8, 8.2, 7.5, 8.0]\n",
    "colores = ['red', 'blue', 'green', 'orange']\n",
    "\n",
    "plt.figure(figsize=(10, 6))\n",
    "\n",
    "# Bar chart\n",
    "barras = plt.bar(regiones, promedios_region, color=colores, alpha=0.7, edgecolor='black')\n",
    "\n",
    "# Añadir valores en las barras\n",
    "for barra, valor in zip(barras, promedios_region):\n",
    "    altura = barra.get_height()\n",
    "    plt.text(barra.get_x() + barra.get_width()/2., altura,\n",
    "             f'{valor:.1f}', ha='center', va='bottom', fontsize=11, fontweight='bold')\n",
    "\n",
    "plt.ylabel('Promedio')\n",
    "plt.title('Promedio por Región')\n",
    "plt.ylim(0, 9)\n",
    "plt.grid(True, alpha=0.3, axis='y')\n",
    "plt.show()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 7. Subplots (Múltiples Gráficos)\n",
    "\n",
    "Mostrar varios gráficos en una misma figura."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Crear figura con 2x2 subplots\n",
    "fig, ((ax1, ax2), (ax3, ax4)) = plt.subplots(2, 2, figsize=(12, 10))\n",
    "\n",
    "# Subplot 1: Línea\n",
    "x = np.linspace(0, 10, 100)\n",
    "ax1.plot(x, np.sin(x), color='blue', linewidth=2)\n",
    "ax1.set_title('Función Seno')\n",
    "ax1.grid(True, alpha=0.3)\n",
    "ax1.set_xlabel('x')\n",
    "ax1.set_ylabel('sin(x)')\n",
    "\n",
    "# Subplot 2: Scatter\n",
    "ax2.scatter(np.random.randn(100), np.random.randn(100), alpha=0.6)\n",
    "ax2.set_title('Datos Aleatorios')\n",
    "ax2.grid(True, alpha=0.3)\n",
    "\n",
    "# Subplot 3: Histograma\n",
    "ax3.hist(np.random.normal(0, 1, 1000), bins=30, color='green', alpha=0.7)\n",
    "ax3.set_title('Distribución Normal')\n",
    "ax3.grid(True, alpha=0.3, axis='y')\n",
    "\n",
    "# Subplot 4: Box plot\n",
    "ax4.boxplot([np.random.normal(0, 1, 100) for _ in range(3)])\n",
    "ax4.set_title('Comparación de Distribuciones')\n",
    "ax4.grid(True, alpha=0.3, axis='y')\n",
    "\n",
    "plt.tight_layout()\n",
    "plt.show()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 8. Visualizar Matrices de Correlación (Heatmap)\n",
    "\n",
    "Muestra la correlación entre múltiples variables."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Crear datos correlacionados\n",
    "np.random.seed(42)\n",
    "datos = np.random.randn(100, 4)\n",
    "# Añadir correlaciones\n",
    "datos[:, 1] = datos[:, 0] + 0.5 * np.random.randn(100)\n",
    "datos[:, 2] = -datos[:, 0] + 0.3 * np.random.randn(100)\n",
    "\n",
    "df_corr = pd.DataFrame(datos, columns=['Variable A', 'Variable B', 'Variable C', 'Variable D'])\n",
    "\n",
    "# Calcular matriz de correlación\n",
    "matriz_corr = df_corr.corr()\n",
    "\n",
    "print(\"Matriz de Correlación:\")\n",
    "print(matriz_corr)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Visualizar como heatmap usando imshow\n",
    "plt.figure(figsize=(8, 6))\n",
    "plt.imshow(matriz_corr, cmap='coolwarm', aspect='auto', vmin=-1, vmax=1)\n",
    "plt.colorbar(label='Correlación')\n",
    "\n",
    "# Etiquetas\n",
    "plt.xticks(range(len(matriz_corr.columns)), matriz_corr.columns, rotation=45, ha='right')\n",
    "plt.yticks(range(len(matriz_corr.columns)), matriz_corr.columns)\n",
    "\n",
    "# Añadir valores en las celdas\n",
    "for i in range(len(matriz_corr)):\n",
    "    for j in range(len(matriz_corr)):\n",
    "        plt.text(j, i, f'{matriz_corr.iloc[i, j]:.2f}', ha='center', va='center', color='black')\n",
    "\n",
    "plt.title('Matriz de Correlación')\n",
    "plt.tight_layout()\n",
    "plt.show()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 9. Gráfico de Curva de Aprendizaje\n",
    "\n",
    "Visualización típica para analizar el desempeño de redes neuronales."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Simular curva de aprendizaje\n",
    "epocas = np.arange(1, 51)\n",
    "# Precisión aumenta y se estabiliza\n",
    "precision_train = 0.5 + 0.45 * (1 - np.exp(-epocas/10)) + np.random.normal(0, 0.01, 50)\n",
    "precision_val = 0.5 + 0.40 * (1 - np.exp(-epocas/12)) + np.random.normal(0, 0.02, 50)\n",
    "\n",
    "plt.figure(figsize=(10, 6))\n",
    "\n",
    "plt.plot(epocas, precision_train, marker='o', label='Entrenamiento', linewidth=2, markersize=4)\n",
    "plt.plot(epocas, precision_val, marker='s', label='Validación', linewidth=2, markersize=4)\n",
    "\n",
    "plt.fill_between(epocas, precision_train, precision_val, alpha=0.2, color='gray', label='Brecha')\n",
    "\n",
    "plt.xlabel('Época')\n",
    "plt.ylabel('Precisión')\n",
    "plt.title('Curva de Aprendizaje de la Red Neuronal')\n",
    "plt.legend()\n",
    "plt.grid(True, alpha=0.3)\n",
    "plt.ylim([0.4, 1.0])\n",
    "plt.show()\n",
    "\n",
    "# Análisis\n",
    "print(f\"Precisión final de entrenamiento: {precision_train[-1]:.3f}\")\n",
    "print(f\"Precisión final de validación: {precision_val[-1]:.3f}\")\n",
    "print(f\"Brecha (overfitting): {(precision_train[-1] - precision_val[-1]):.3f}\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 10. Personalización Avanzada\n",
    "\n",
    "Técnicas para mejorar la apariencia de los gráficos."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": {"execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Cambiar estilos disponibles\n",
    "print(\"Estilos disponibles:\")\n",
    "print(plt.style.available[:5])  # Mostrar algunos estilos\n",
    "\n",
    "# Usar un estilo\n",
    "plt.style.use('seaborn-v0_8-darkgrid')\n",
    "\n",
    "# Crear gráfico con estilo personalizado\n",
    "x = np.linspace(0, 2*np.pi, 100)\n",
    "plt.figure(figsize=(12, 5))\n",
    "\n",
    "plt.plot(x, np.sin(x), linewidth=2.5, label='sin(x)', color='#1f77b4')\n",
    "plt.plot(x, np.cos(x), linewidth=2.5, label='cos(x)', color='#ff7f0e')\n",
    "plt.plot(x, np.tan(x), linewidth=2.5, label='tan(x)', color='#2ca02c', alpha=0.7)\n",
    "\n",
    "plt.xlabel('x', fontsize=12, fontweight='bold')\n",
    "plt.ylabel('y', fontsize=12, fontweight='bold')\n",
    "plt.title('Funciones Trigonométricas', fontsize=14, fontweight='bold')\n",
    "plt.legend(fontsize=11)\n",
    "plt.grid(True, alpha=0.4)\n",
    "plt.ylim(-3, 3)\n",
    "plt.tight_layout()\n",
    "plt.show()\n",
    "\n",
    "# Restaurar estilo por defecto\n",
    "plt.style.use('default')"
   ]
  },
  {
